    "locales": {
      "en": {
        "name": "Carcano M1891 6.5x52 bolt-action Carbine",
        "shortName": "M1891 Carbine",
        "description": "Adopted on 9 June 1893, for cavalry, carabinieri, and later for cyclists, it uses a walnut stock with a folding bayonet beneath the muzzle. the bolt handle was bent down. These guns were produced exclusively by the Brescia Arsenal until its foreclosure in 1922, then they got produced by other Arsenals (Terni and Gardone Val Trompia) and Private industries (F.N.A., Beretta). Informally nicknamed \"Cavalry Carcano\" or \"Moschetto\" (Italian for \"carbine\"), it was used by the Italian Army until the end of World War II, and by the Italian Navy until 1970. It was also used by the Italian Social Republic and various partisan groups during World War II, and by the Italian police forces until the 1980s."
      }
    },
